# Design System Guidelines

## Typography System

### Font Families
- **Headings**: Always use `font-heading` class (Poppins font family)
- **Body text**: Always use `font-body` class (Inter font family)
- **Custom fonts**: Use `font-chillax` for special cases only

### Typography Classes
Use these predefined classes instead of custom styling:

```tsx
// Headings
<h1 className="heading-primary">Main Title</h1>
<h2 className="heading-secondary">Section Title</h2>
<h3 className="heading-tertiary">Subsection Title</h3>

// Body text
<p className="body-text">Regular paragraph text</p>
<p className="text-large">Larger body text</p>
<span className="text-emphasis">Emphasized text</span>
<span className="brand-text">Brand/accent text</span>
```

### Text Sizes
- **Primary headings**: `text-4xl lg:text-5xl` or `heading-primary`
- **Secondary headings**: `text-2xl lg:text-3xl` or `heading-secondary`
- **Tertiary headings**: `text-xl lg:text-2xl` or `heading-tertiary`
- **Body text**: `text-lg` or `text-large`
- **Small text**: `text-sm` or `text-base`

## Color System

### Primary Colors
- **Gamboge (Primary)**: `#E49B0F` - Use `text-primary`, `bg-primary`, `border-primary`
- **Licorice (Secondary)**: `#20000C` - Use `licorice-text`, `licorice-background`
- **Antique White (Background)**: `#FAEBD7` - Use `antique-white-text`, `bg-background`

### Color Classes
Always use these predefined color classes:

```tsx
// Text colors
<span className="text-primary">Gamboge text</span>
<span className="licorice-text">Dark text</span>
<span className="antique-white-text">Light text</span>
<span className="gamboge-text">Accent text</span>

// Background colors
<div className="bg-primary">Gamboge background</div>
<div className="licorice-background">Dark background</div>
<div className="gamboge-background">Accent background</div>

// Border colors
<div className="border-primary">Gamboge border</div>
```

### Color Usage Guidelines
- **Primary actions**: Use `text-primary` or `bg-primary`
- **Secondary content**: Use `licorice-text` or `text-foreground`
- **Backgrounds**: Use `bg-background` for main backgrounds
- **Accents**: Use `text-primary` for highlights and CTAs
- **Muted text**: Use `text-foreground/80` or `licorice-text/80`

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
```tsx
// Primary button
<button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground font-heading font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg">
  Primary Action
</button>

// Secondary button
<button className="border border-primary text-primary font-heading font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg">
  Secondary Action
</button>
```

### Cards
```tsx
<div className="bg-card text-card-foreground border border-border rounded-lg p-6">
  <h3 className="heading-tertiary mb-3">Card Title</h3>
  <p className="body-text">Card content</p>
</div>
```

### Feature Badges
```tsx
// Use alternating brand colors for variety
<div className="bg-primary/10 text-primary border border-primary/20 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-body">
  Feature Badge
</div>
```

## Accessibility Requirements

### Color Contrast
- Ensure minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio for normal text
- Ensure minimum 3:1 contrast ratio for large text
- Test with both light and dark backgrounds

### Typography
- Use semantic HTML elements (`h1`, `h2`, `p`, etc.)
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy
- Use `font-body` for readable body text

## Common Anti-Patterns to Avoid

❌ **Don't use hardcoded colors:**
```tsx
// Bad
<span className="text-[#E49B0F]">Text</span>
<div className="bg-[#20000C]">Background</div>

// Good
<span className="text-primary">Text</span>
<div className="licorice-background">Background</div>
```

❌ **Don't use custom font sizes without classes:**
```tsx
// Bad
<h2 className="text-3xl font-bold">Title</h2>

// Good
<h2 className="heading-secondary">Title</h2>
```

❌ **Don't mix font families:**
```tsx
// Bad
<h1 className="font-sans text-4xl">Title</h1>

// Good
<h1 className="font-heading heading-primary">Title</h1>
```

## Implementation Checklist

When creating new components:

- [ ] Use `font-heading` for all headings
- [ ] Use `font-body` for all body text
- [ ] Use predefined color classes (`text-primary`, `licorice-text`, etc.)
- [ ] Use typography classes (`heading-primary`, `body-text`, etc.)
- [ ] Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- [ ] Test with both light and dark themes
- [ ] Use semantic HTML elements
- [ ] Follow established component patterns

